{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-30T03:54:29.919126157Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-485691a3","body":"`src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:416` soft-resets directly to freshly fetched `origin/master` without first proving that `origin/master` is already an ancestor of the feature branch. If master advanced after the checkpoint branch was created, `git reset --soft origin/master` leaves the index at the old checkpoint tree; the commit at `src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:443` can then include reversions or deletions for unrelated upstream changes. Add an ancestry check such as `git merge-base --is-ancestor origin/master HEAD` before the reset, or fail with a rebase/sync hint, and cover the advanced-master case in the mock port tests.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"03043818646565b1f805065712182b80a4d15e27361595a1251d271f7e2a7a2d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260430030405","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-30T03:54:29.939657365Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-02617c1e","body":"`src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:258` collects only commit subjects, and `src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:405` treats any subject starting with `rb: checkpoint` as safe to squash. That does not enforce the requested safety check: a hand-written commit with a matching prefix, or a checkpoint from another project/run, is silently subsumed. Return full commit messages and validate them with the existing checkpoint metadata parser, ideally matching the active project/run, before allowing the reset. Add a regression for a commit titled `rb: checkpoint manual` with no `RB-*` body.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"a7422ffa9bdd3b9d276621c73b6b8fec4d71bb38885e26777147c2ad857ec513","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260430030405","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":22,"timestamp":"2026-04-30T03:54:29.963554791Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-322ee87c","body":"`open_pr_for_completed_run` runs gates on the working tree at `src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:382`, then soft-resets and commits only the staged index at `src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:416` and `src/contexts/bead_workflow/pr_open.rs:443`. There is no guard for unstaged real-code changes before the reset. If a user or late tool leaves `src/` or `tests/` edits unstaged, the gates can pass against code that the PR commit omits. Add a pre-reset dirty-worktree check excluding allowed live `.ralph-burning/` state, or explicitly stage the intended real-code paths after reset, with a test that unstaged product changes fail before push.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"2265f533c912b2b1798fb428bddf772270d6979fe618ae9e4899e4bfdcdbbc69","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260430030405","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
